originContent: Cross-Platform Dell Power Manager re-implementation in Flutter. More screenshots in [Wiki](https://github.com/alexVinarskis/dell-powermanager/wiki).
translatedContent: Cross-Platform Dell Power Manager re-implementation in Flutter. More screenshots in [Wiki](https://github.com/alexVinarskis/dell-powermanager/wiki).

originContent: Dell machines (XPS and Precision series laptops, potentially others) offer advanced in-bios configurable options, such as multiple thermal profiles, battery charging thresholds, etc. It may be very desirable to adjust these on the go, and there is no way to configure it from OS without Dell's proprietary tools (which are luckily provided). Settings can be changed via:
translatedContent: Dell machines (XPS and Precision series laptops, potentially others) offer advanced in-bios configurable options, such as multiple thermal profiles, battery charging thresholds, etc. It may be very desirable to adjust these on the go, and there is no way to configure it from OS without Dell's proprietary tools (which are luckily provided). Settings can be changed via:

originContent: * [Dell Command | Configure](https://www.dell.com/support/kbdoc/en-us/000178000/dell-command-configure) CLI, available for both Windows and Linux, with impressive [list of capabilities](https://dl.dell.com/topicspdf/command-configure_reference-guide4_en-us.pdf).
translatedContent: * [Dell Command | Configure](https://www.dell.com/support/kbdoc/en-us/000178000/dell-command-configure) CLI, available for both Windows and Linux, with impressive [list of capabilities](https://dl.dell.com/topicspdf/command-configure_reference-guide4_en-us.pdf).

originContent: * [Dell Power Manager](https://www.dell.com/support/contents/en-au/article/product-support/self-support-knowledgebase/software-and-downloads/dell-power-manager) GUI, available for Windows only. On top of that, it is ridiculously slow to start, and (subjectively) ugly.
translatedContent: * [Dell Power Manager](https://www.dell.com/support/contents/en-au/article/product-support/self-support-knowledgebase/software-and-downloads/dell-power-manager) GUI, available for Windows only. On top of that, it is ridiculously slow to start, and (subjectively) ugly.

originContent: This app is a modern, Flutter based GUI on top of Dell Command | Configure CLI, with main goal to replicate behavior of Dell Power Manager for Linux users, but also does run on Windows.
translatedContent: This app is a modern, Flutter based GUI on top of Dell Command | Configure CLI, with main goal to replicate behavior of Dell Power Manager for Linux users, but also does run on Windows.

originContent: * Implements control via 'Dell Command | Configure CLI' (CCTK)
translatedContent: * Implements control via 'Dell Command | Configure CLI' (CCTK)

originContent: * Modern animated UI, supports Dark Mode
translatedContent: * Modern animated UI, supports Dark Mode

originContent: * Short startup time, much faster than Dell's Windows app
translatedContent: * Short startup time, much faster than Dell's Windows app

originContent: * Detects and handles unsupported modes on supported machines
translatedContent: * Detects and handles unsupported modes on supported machines

originContent: * Detects non-dell machines, shows error message
translatedContent: * Detects non-dell machines, shows error message

originContent: * Support protected BIOS (System/Setup/Owner passwords), and secure key saving
translatedContent: * Support protected BIOS (System/Setup/Owner passwords), and secure key saving

originContent: For Debian/Ubuntu based Linux and Windows, app is slightly more productized:
translatedContent: For Debian/Ubuntu based Linux and Windows, app is slightly more productized:

originContent: * Packaged to `.deb`/`.msi`, with start menu shortcuts etc.
translatedContent: * Packaged to `.deb`/`.msi`, with start menu shortcuts etc.

originContent: * Battery charging control (w/o advanced/daily timing mode for now)
translatedContent: * Battery charging control (w/o advanced/daily timing mode for now)

originContent: * Add monitoring service for auto switching thermal profiles based on CPU load
translatedContent: * Add monitoring service for auto switching thermal profiles based on CPU load

originContent: * Add monitoring service for auto switching thermal profiles based on power settings, eg. Battery level, plug/unplugged etc.
translatedContent: * Add monitoring service for auto switching thermal profiles based on power settings, eg. Battery level, plug/unplugged etc.

originContent: Application is currently in **stable, maintained** state.
translatedContent: Application is currently in **stable, maintained** state.

originContent: * Dell's CCTK integrated (with automated installer for select OSs)
translatedContent: * Dell's CCTK integrated (with automated installer for select OSs)

originContent: * Update checks implemented (with OTA ia Github API for select OSs)
translatedContent: * Update checks implemented (with OTA ia Github API for select OSs)

originContent: * UI tested, build and packaging asserted by CI
translatedContent: * UI tested, build and packaging asserted by CI

originContent: * Run from source via `flutter run`, build via `flutter build linux --release`
translatedContent: * Run from source via `flutter run`, build via `flutter build linux --release`

originContent: ATTENTION: do _not_ install flutter from `snap`, you native [installation instead](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/linux/desktop) - snap-provided flutter will fail to compile for this project due to [snap specific issues](https://github.com/juliansteenbakker/flutter_secure_storage/issues/676).
translatedContent: ATTENTION: do _not_ install flutter from `snap`, use native [installation instead](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/linux/desktop) - snap-provided flutter will fail to compile for this project due to [snap specific issues](https://github.com/juliansteenbakker/flutter_secure_storage/issues/676).

translatedContent: * Run from source via `flutter run`, build via `flutter build windows --release`

originContent: By default, all logging is supressed. Export `POWERMANAGER_DEBUG=true` before running app from CLI to get logs.
translatedContent: By default, all logging is suppressed. Export `POWERMANAGER_DEBUG=true` before running app from CLI to get logs.

originContent: Eg.: `export POWERMANAGER_DEBUG=true && ./dell-powermanager > file.log`. When opening an issue, kindly save and attach the log.
translatedContent: Eg.: `export POWERMANAGER_DEBUG=true && ./dell-powermanager > file.log`. When opening an issue, kindly save and attach the log.
